 6ï¸âƒ£ Remote Access to EC2 (Connection Concepts)

â†’ EC2 server remote hota hai
â†’ Usko access karne ke liye secure connection chahiye

---

 ğŸ”‘ Key Pair (Public Key and Private Key)

â†’ Key pair = Security for login
â†’ Public Key server me store hoti hai
â†’ Private Key tumhare system me hoti hai

â†’ Jab connect karte ho
Private key verify hoti hai
Agar match hui â†’ login allowed

â†’ Without key pair
EC2 access possible nahi

---

 7ï¸âƒ£ SSH (Secure Shell)

â†’ SSH = Secure Shell Protocol
â†’ Secure tarike se server ko remotely control karne ka method

â†’ EC2 me
SSH se Linux server connect hota hai

â†’ Example
Browser nahi, terminal se server access
Commands run karte ho
Software install karte ho
Website deploy karte ho

---

 8ï¸âƒ£ PuTTY (Windows Users)

â†’ PuTTY ek SSH client hai
â†’ Windows me Linux EC2 se connect hone ke liye use hota hai

â†’ Steps concept
Private key (.ppk file)
â†’ PuTTY me load hoti hai
â†’ Secure login ho jata hai

---

 9ï¸âƒ£ SSL Certificate

â†’ SSL = Secure Sockets Layer
â†’ Website ke liye security certificate

â†’ Kya karta hai
Data encrypt karta hai
User aur server ke beech secure communication deta hai

â†’ Result
Website https:// se open hoti hai
Browser me â€œSecureâ€ dikhta hai

---

 ğŸ”— How All These Are Connected in AWS EC2

â†’ Tumne Linux EC2 instance launch kiya
â†’ Key Pair create ki for secure login
â†’ SSH ke through server me login kiya
â†’ Root/admin permissions se software install kiya
â†’ Apache Web Server (httpd) install kiya
â†’ HTML file banayi (`index.html`)
â†’ Browser me URL (IP address) dala
â†’ HTTP / HTTPS ke through website internet par live ho gayi
â†’ Future me SSL certificate lagakar HTTPS enable kiya ja sakta hai

---

 ğŸ”§ Create Linux Web Server on AWS EC2 (Concept Flow)

â†’ EC2 launch (Amazon Linux)
â†’ Key pair attach (for login)
â†’ Security group allow HTTP (80) & SSH (22)
â†’ SSH se server connect
â†’ Apache install
â†’ HTML file create
â†’ Browser me website verify

