 âš™ï¸ 11ï¸âƒ£ Bash Script (User Data) â€“ Line by Line Breakdown

 ğŸ“Œ Script:

```bash
!/bin/bash
yum update -y
yum install httpd -y
echo " <html><body><center><h1>I am a great person I Have Lunched EC2</h1></center></body></html> " > /var/www/html/index.html
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
```

---

 ğŸ” Line-by-Line Explanation

â†’ `!/bin/bash`
Tells system â†’ Ye bash script hai

â†’ `yum update -y`
System ke packages update karta hai

â†’ `yum install httpd -y`
Apache Web Server install karta hai

â†’ `echo "HTML code" > /var/www/html/index.html`
HTML content ko website ke main page me likh deta hai
`/var/www/html/` = Apache ka default web folder

â†’ `systemctl start httpd`
Web server start karta hai

â†’ `systemctl enable httpd`
Server reboot ke baad bhi Apache automatically start ho

