 ğŸ“œ Bash Script Breakdown (Day 16)

```bash
!/bin/bash
yum update -y
yum install httpd -y
echo " <html><body><center><h1>I am a great person I Have Lunched EC2</h1></center></body></html> " > /var/www/html/index.html
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
```

---

 ğŸ”¹ `!/bin/bash` â†’ Shebang

â†’ **Shebang** batata hai ki ye file **kaunse interpreter se run hogi**
â†’ `/bin/bash` ka matlab hai **Bash shell** use karo
â†’ System ko pata chalta hai ki ye **bash script** hai

---

 ğŸ”¹ `bin` â†’ Binary Files

â†’ `bin` ka matlab hota hai **binary executables ka folder**
â†’ `/bin/bash` = Bash program ka location
â†’ Linux me important commands (`ls`, `cp`, `mv`, `bash`) yahin hote hain

---

 ğŸ”¹ `yum` â†’ Package Installer

â†’ **YUM = Yellowdog Updater Modified**
â†’ Amazon Linux / RHEL me software install, update, remove karne ka tool
â†’ Internet se packages download karta hai

---

 ğŸ”¹ `yum update -y`

â†’ System ke **saare installed packages update** karta hai
â†’ `-y` ka matlab â†’ automatic **Yes** (confirmation nahi maangta)

ğŸ‘‰ EC2 me use:
Server ko latest security patches mil jaate hain

---

 ğŸ”¹ `yum install httpd -y`

â†’ **httpd = Apache Web Server**
â†’ Ye command Apache install karti hai
â†’ `-y` â†’ automatic yes

ğŸ‘‰ EC2 me use:
Yehi software tumhari **website ko serve** karega

---

 ğŸ”¹ `httpd` â†’ Apache Web Server

â†’ `httpd` ka full form â†’ **HTTP Daemon**
â†’ Ye ek **web server software** hai
â†’ Browser se request aati hai â†’ httpd HTML page bhejta hai

ğŸ‘‰ Tumhari EC2 machine:
Server ban jaati hai jo website host karti hai

---

 ğŸ”¹ `echo` â†’ Print Command

â†’ `echo` ka kaam hota hai **text print karna**
â†’ Screen par ya kisi file me text likhna

Example:

```bash
echo "Hello World"
```

---

 ğŸ”¹ `> /var/www/html/index.html`

â†’ `>` ka matlab â†’ **output ko file me likhna**
â†’ `/var/www/html/` = Apache ka **default web folder**
â†’ `index.html` = Website ka main page

ğŸ‘‰ Is line ka matlab:
HTML code ko **website ke home page** me daal diya

---

 ğŸ”¹ `systemctl` â†’ Service Controller

â†’ `systemctl` Linux me **services ko manage** karta hai
â†’ Start, stop, restart, enable services

---

 ğŸ”¹ `systemctl start httpd`

â†’ Apache web server ko **start karta hai**
â†’ Ab website browser se access ho sakti hai

---

 ğŸ”¹ `systemctl enable httpd`

â†’ Server reboot ke baad bhi **Apache automatically start ho**
â†’ Permanent service bana deta hai

---

 ğŸ”— How This Script Works in AWS EC2 (Connected Flow)

â†’ EC2 Linux instance start hota hai
â†’ Ye bash script automatically run hoti hai (User Data)
â†’ System update hota hai
â†’ Apache install hota hai
â†’ HTML file create hoti hai
â†’ Apache start hota hai
â†’ Website **public IP / URL** se live ho jaati hai

---

 ğŸ§  One-Line Summary

â†’ **Shebang** = Script ka interpreter
â†’ **bin** = Binary programs ka folder
â†’ **yum** = Software installer
â†’ **httpd** = Apache web server
â†’ **echo** = Text print/write command
â†’ **systemctl** = Service manager


